# <%= it.displayName %>

<%= it.description %>

Built with [FastAPI](https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/) and [fastapi-mcp](https://github.com/tadata-org/fastapi_mcp), which auto-exposes your FastAPI endpoints as MCP tools.

## Getting started

```bash
uv sync
uv run uvicorn main:app --reload --port <%= it.port %>
```

The MCP server is available at `http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>`.

## Connect to MCP clients

### Claude Desktop

**Option A — mcp-remote proxy (works on all Claude Desktop versions):**

Add to `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json` (macOS) or
`%APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json` (Windows):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<%= it.serverName %>": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote", "http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>"]
    }
  }
}
```

**Option B — native URL (if your Claude Desktop is recent enough):**

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<%= it.serverName %>": {
      "url": "http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>"
    }
  }
}
```

Option A requires Node.js but works on all Claude Desktop versions. If Option B works for you, you can remove Option A.

### Claude Code (CLI)

```bash
claude mcp add --transport http <%= it.serverName %> http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>
```

### Cursor

Add to `~/.cursor/mcp.json` (global) or `.cursor/mcp.json` (project):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<%= it.serverName %>": {
      "url": "http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>"
    }
  }
}
```

## Development

```bash
# Run tests
uv run pytest

# Lint
uv run ruff check .

# Format
uv run ruff format .
```

## Security

When deploying outside localhost, enforce authentication at the transport layer
(OAuth 2.1 + PKCE for Streamable HTTP per the MCP specification).

---

This project was generated with production standards applied — see [STANDARDS.md](STANDARDS.md) for what was applied and why.

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `LOG_LEVEL` | `info` | Logging verbosity. One of `debug`, `info`, `warn`, `error`. |
| `RATE_LIMIT_MAX` | `100` | Max requests per minute per client (HTTP variants only). |
